{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "A recent study by Cardon et al. (2023) found that many writing instructors were concerned about the potential impact of AI-powered writing tools on their jobs.",
    "Some felt that AI would take away their jobs, while others were concerned about the quality of writing that could be produced using AI.",
    "The research by Macdonald et al. (2023) and Marchandot et al. (2023) suggest that these concerns may be founded.",
    "Instructors in higher education fear the potential of GPT to be used for academic dishonesty (Cotton et al., 2023; Pickell & Doak., 2023).",
    "In a recent survey of 1000 college students, 51% reported that they believe that the use of AI constitutes cheating or plagiarism (though 20% admitted to using them; Welding, 2023)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "A recent study by Cardon et al. (2023) found that many writing instructors were concerned about the potential impact of AI-powered writing tools on their jobs.",
    "The research by Macdonald et al. (2023) and Marchandot et al. (2023) suggest that these concerns may be founded.",
    "Instructors in higher education fear the potential of GPT to be used for academic dishonesty (Cotton et al., 2023; Pickell & Doak., 2023).",
    "In a recent survey of 1000 college students, 51% reported that they believe that the use of AI constitutes cheating or plagiarism (though 20% admitted to using them; Welding, 2023)."
